HEADWORD: Oreodon
<hw>O"re*o*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'o`ros</grk>, <grk>-eos</grk>, mountain + <grk>'odoy`s</grk>,
<grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, tooth.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
extinct herbivorous mammals, abundant in the Tertiary formation of the
Rocky Mountains. It is more or less related to the camel, hog, and
deer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

